      { q: "Which is the correct way to use 「Operationalization (조작적 정의)」 in a thesis?", options: ["In mixed or exploratory studies, state that the study follows abductive logic—explaining data-derived patterns with existing theory.", "In the theoretical background, explicitly state 'In this study, X is defined as Y.'", "State at the start of methodology that this study is grounded in [paradigm] to strengthen overall methodological coherence.", "Stating that coding reliability was pre-validated through a pilot study increases methodological rigor."], answer: 1, explanation: "In the theoretical background, explicitly state 'In this study, X is defined as Y.'" },
      { q: "The following is a problem noted in the 「Research Purpose & Questions」 section. Which rejection pattern is it?\n\"연구목적이 RQ보다 더 구체적으로 서술되거나, RQ가 목적보다 더 추상적인 역전 구조. 목적(추상적·포괄적) → RQ(구체적·조작적)의 위계가 유지되어야 한다.\"", options: ["Reversed hierarchy of purpose and RQs", "Yes/no format RQ", "Misalignment of subject, perspective, and direction", "Missing logical connection among RQs"], answer: 0, explanation: "Reversed hierarchy of purpose and RQs — 연구목적이 RQ보다 더 구체적으로 서술되거나, RQ가 목적보다 더 추상적인 역전 구조. 목적(추상적·포괄적) → RQ(구체적·조작적)의 위계가 유지되어야 한다." },
      { q: "Which is the correct way to use 「Reliability (신뢰도)」 in a thesis?", options: ["Key step in the research background: prior studies addressed X but not Y. This is the gap the present study fills.", "MDS results appear as coordinate plots; closer distance means more similar perception, farther means more opposing.", "Applied to AI creation news, policy documents, and online comments via critical discourse analysis (CDA).", "Cohen's kappa ≥ .80 is recognized as almost perfect agreement—high reliability."], answer: 3, explanation: "Cohen's kappa ≥ .80 is recognized as almost perfect agreement—high reliability." },
      { q: "[True/False] The definition of 「Research Question」 is \"Research purpose converted into concrete, investigable questions—the core questions the entire study must answer.\".", options: ["True", "False"], answer: 0, explanation: "Correct. Research purpose converted into concrete, investigable questions—the core questions the entire study must answer." },
      { q: "Which is the correct way to use 「Research Question (연구문제, RQ)」 in a thesis?", options: ["Citing Braun & Clarke's (2006) six-step procedure (familiarization → initial codes → theme search → theme review → theme naming → report) strengthens methodological credibility.", "Qualitative results with specific quotes and context alongside numbers achieve thick description.", "Good RQs are not yes/no; they take the form of how, why, or what type.", "In the theoretical background, explicitly state 'In this study, X is defined as Y.'"], answer: 2, explanation: "Good RQs are not yes/no; they take the form of how, why, or what type." },
      { q: "Which narrative pattern receives a 'good evaluation' in the 「Research Purpose & Questions」 section?", options: ["Unclear research scope", "Too many objectives", "Yes/no format RQ", "Analysis–interpretation structure"], answer: 3, explanation: "「Analysis–interpretation structure」 is a recommended good narrative pattern." },
      { q: "The following is a problem noted in the 「Research Purpose & Questions」 section. Which rejection pattern is it?\n\"6~8개의 세부 목적을 나열하여 연구 초점이 분산되는 경우. 논문에서는 핵심 목적 1개 + 세부 목적 3~4개가 적정 구조이다.\"", options: ["Missing logical connection among RQs", "Too many objectives", "Overlap between RQ and purpose", "Vague objective"], answer: 1, explanation: "Too many objectives — 6~8개의 세부 목적을 나열하여 연구 초점이 분산되는 경우. 논문에서는 핵심 목적 1개 + 세부 목적 3~4개가 적정 구조이다." },
      { q: "다음 정의에 해당하는 연구방법은?\n\"단일 시점 표준화 설문 자료 수집\"", options: ["QN-8 Meta-Analysis", "QN-1 True Experiment", "QN-6 Cross-Sectional Survey", "QN-3 Correlational Study"], answer: 2, explanation: "QN-6 Cross-Sectional Survey — 단일 시점 표준화 설문 자료 수집" },
      { q: "Which concept does the following analogy describe?\n\"연구라는 여행의 목적지. RQ1이 서울에서 부산까지 가는 길은 몇 가지인가? 라면 RQ2는 각 길의 특징은 무엇인가? RQ3은 어떤 길이 왜 더 효율적인가? 처럼…\"", options: ["Ontology", "Research Paradigm", "Epistemology", "Research Question"], answer: 3, explanation: "Research Question" },
      { q: "The following is a problem noted in the 「Research Purpose & Questions」 section. Which rejection pattern is it?\n\"연구 대상, 분석 관점, 연구 방향이 각각 다른 장에서 다르게 서술되어 일관성이 없는 경우. 연구목적 문장에서 설정한 세 요소가 전 장에 걸쳐 일관되어야 한다.\"", options: ["Misalignment of subject, perspective, and direction", "Use of abstract verbs", "Presenting method as purpose", "Disconnected from background"], answer: 0, explanation: "Misalignment of subject, perspective, and direction — 연구 대상, 분석 관점, 연구 방향이 각각 다른 장에서 다르게 서술되어 일관성이 없는 경우. 연구목적 문장에서 설정한 세 요소가 전 장에 걸쳐 일관되어야 한다." },
      { q: "Which is the correct way to use 「Purposive Sampling (목적 표집)」 in a thesis?", options: ["The goal is not mere summary but to derive what has not yet been studied in the field.", "Most common in qualitative research; selection criteria must be clearly stated for justification.", "State in methodology: 'Member checking with five participants was conducted to verify accuracy of findings.'", "Stating that coding reliability was pre-validated through a pilot study increases methodological rigor."], answer: 1, explanation: "Most common in qualitative research; selection criteria must be clearly stated for justification." },
      { q: "[True/False] The definition of 「Pilot Study」 is \"A small-scale trial conducted before the main study to review design and methodological issues in advance.\".", options: ["True", "False"], answer: 0, explanation: "Correct. A small-scale trial conducted before the main study to review design and methodological issues in advance." }
