      content: "<div class=\"easy\">연구 공백(<span class=\"term\">Research Gap</span>) — in a nutshell: An area of scholarly omission or insufficient coverage in prior research.<br/>If a term is new, recall \"why it is needed\" before the name itself.</div><div class=\"example\"><strong>🟢 Understand through analogy</strong><br/>uncharted territory on the map of existing AI research. If prior work thoroughly analyzed AI's technical performance but not how the general public perceives AI-created works—that unexplored area is the research gap.</div><h3>Precise definition</h3><p>An area of scholarly omission or insufficient coverage in prior research.</p><div class=\"highlight\"><strong>📝 How to use this in a thesis</strong><br/>Key step in the research background: prior studies addressed X but not Y. This is the gap the present study fills.</div><div class=\"example\"><strong>✍️ Example sentence</strong><br/>\"This study <span class=\"term\">연구 공백</span>의 관점에서 ○○을(를) 분석한다.\". Identify where in your study this concept applies—in one sentence..</div><p class=\"term\"><strong>One-line summary</strong> · 연구 공백 = An area of scholarly omission or insufficient coverage in prior research.</p>",
