      { q: "[True/False] The definition of 「Research Gap」 is \"An area of scholarly omission or insufficient coverage in prior research.\".", options: ["True", "False"], answer: 0, explanation: "Correct. An area of scholarly omission or insufficient coverage in prior research." },
      { q: "[True/False] The definition of 「Research Question」 is \"Research purpose converted into concrete, investigable questions—the core questions the entire study must answer.\".", options: ["True", "False"], answer: 0, explanation: "Correct. Research purpose converted into concrete, investigable questions—the core questions the entire study must answer." },
      { q: "Which is the correct way to use 「Cohens Kappa (코헨의 카파)」 in a thesis?", options: ["A separate Researcher Positionality section in qualitative methodology increases scholarly credibility.", "Report Cohen's kappa κ=.84, p<.001 with statistical significance when reporting coding reliability in qualitative research.", "Key step in the research background: prior studies addressed X but not Y. This is the gap the present study fills.", "In the theoretical background, explicitly state 'In this study, X is defined as Y.'"], answer: 1, explanation: "Report Cohen's kappa κ=.84, p<.001 with statistical significance when reporting coding reliability in qualitative research." },
      { q: "[True/False] The definition of 「Cohens Kappa」 is \"The systematic review, analysis, and synthesis of existing scholarly work related to the research topic.\".", options: ["True", "False"], answer: 1, explanation: "The correct definition of 「Cohens Kappa」: The systematic review, analysis, and synthesis of existing scholarly work related to the research topic." },
      { q: "Which is the best definition of 「Saturation (포화)  (Data Saturation / Theoretical Saturation)」?", options: ["An area of scholarly omission or insufficient coverage in prior research.", "A philosophical stance on how the researcher understands the world and knowledge—e.g., interpretivism, positivism, critical theory.", "Analyzing how language produces meaning in social context and reflects power relations.", "In qualitative research, the point when no new themes or codes emerge—criteria for stopping data collection."], answer: 3, explanation: "Saturation: In qualitative research, the point when no new themes or codes emerge—criteria for stopping data collection." },
      { q: "Which concept does the following analogy describe?\n\"연구라는 여행의 목적지. RQ1이 서울에서 부산까지 가는 길은 몇 가지인가? 라면 RQ2는 각 길의 특징은 무엇인가? RQ3은 어떤 길이 왜 더 효율적인가? 처럼…\"", options: ["Research Question", "Member Checking", "Grounded Theory", "Reflexivity"], answer: 0, explanation: "Research Question" },
      { q: "Which concept does the following analogy describe?\n\"번역 결과를 원어민에게 확인받기. 연구자가 인터뷰 내용을 코딩한 후, 참여자에게 제가 이렇게 해석했는데 맞나요? 라고 확인받는 것. 도구적 수용형으로 분류된 참여…\"", options: ["Purposive Sampling", "Ontology", "Theoretical Contribution", "Member Checking"], answer: 3, explanation: "Member Checking" },
      { q: "Which is the best definition of 「Reflexivity (성찰성/연구자 위치성)」?", options: ["The consistency of results when the study is repeated under the same conditions—the consistency of measurement.", "How the study extends, revises, or newly proposes existing theory or conceptual understanding.", "Recognizing and reflecting on how the researcher's background, perspective, and bias may influence the research process and findings.", "A research design integrating qualitative and quantitative methods in one study."], answer: 2, explanation: "Reflexivity: Recognizing and reflecting on how the researcher's background, perspective, and bias may influence the research process and findings." },
      { q: "Which is the correct way to use 「Reflexivity (성찰성/연구자 위치성)」 in a thesis?", options: ["MDS results appear as coordinate plots; closer distance means more similar perception, farther means more opposing.", "Stating that coding reliability was pre-validated through a pilot study increases methodological rigor.", "Good RQs are not yes/no; they take the form of how, why, or what type.", "A separate Researcher Positionality section in qualitative methodology increases scholarly credibility."], answer: 3, explanation: "A separate Researcher Positionality section in qualitative methodology increases scholarly credibility." },
      { q: "Which term matches the following description?\n\"In qualitative research, the point when no new themes or codes emerge—criteria for stopping data collection.\"", options: ["Operationalization", "Triangulation", "Saturation", "Generalizability"], answer: 2, explanation: "Saturation — In qualitative research, the point when no new themes or codes emerge—criteria for stopping data collection." },
      { q: "Which is the best definition of 「Member Checking (구성원 확인)」?", options: ["A validity technique in qualitative research: showing interpretations and conclusions to participants for accuracy confirmation.", "Inferring the hypothesis that best explains observed phenomena—logic between induction (data → theory) and deduction (theory → data).", "In qualitative research, the point when no new themes or codes emerge—criteria for stopping data collection.", "Recognizing and reflecting on how the researcher's background, perspective, and bias may influence the research process and findings."], answer: 0, explanation: "Member Checking: A validity technique in qualitative research: showing interpretations and conclusions to participants for accuracy confirmation." },
      { q: "Which is the best definition of 「Cohens Kappa (코헨의 카파)」?", options: ["A statistic (0–1) measuring agreement when two raters (coders) independently classify the same data.", "A mixed method that identifies subjective perception types by having participants sort statement cards subjectively.", "The conceptual and theoretical structure used to analyze phenomena in a study—it determines which lens is applied.", "Recognizing and reflecting on how the researcher's background, perspective, and bias may influence the research process and findings."], answer: 0, explanation: "Cohens Kappa: A statistic (0–1) measuring agreement when two raters (coders) independently classify the same data." },
      { q: "Which concept does the following analogy describe?\n\"판사가 자신의 개인적 경험이 판결에 영향을 미칠 수 있음을 인식하고 스스로 점검하는 것. AI 예술에 호의적인 연구자는 코딩 시 긍정적 표현을 더 쉽게 포착할 수…\"", options: ["Research Gap", "Literature Review", "IRB", "Reflexivity"], answer: 3, explanation: "Reflexivity" },
      { q: "Which term matches the following description?\n\"A statistic (0–1) measuring agreement when two raters (coders) independently classify the same data.\"", options: ["IRB", "Cohens Kappa", "Q Methodology", "Research Question"], answer: 1, explanation: "Cohens Kappa — A statistic (0–1) measuring agreement when two raters (coders) independently classify the same data." },
      { q: "Which is the correct way to use 「Research Question (연구문제, RQ)」 in a thesis?", options: ["Citing IRB approval number 2023-XXX in methodology officially demonstrates ethical compliance.", "State in methodology: 'From the 15th interview, no new themes emerged; theoretical saturation was confirmed and data collection ended.'", "State in methodology: 'Member checking with five participants was conducted to verify accuracy of findings.'", "Good RQs are not yes/no; they take the form of how, why, or what type."], answer: 3, explanation: "Good RQs are not yes/no; they take the form of how, why, or what type." }
